  "prompt": "How do I book a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride?",
  "response": "Booking a round trip on Uber such that it is counted as a single ride is not a standard feature offered by the Uber app. However, there are a few workarounds you can try:\n\n### 1. **Coordinate with the Driver:**\n   - **Discuss with the Driver:** When your driver arrives, explain that you need a round trip and ask if they can wait for you at your destination before taking you back. Most drivers are willing to accommodate this if they know in advance.\n   - **Pause the Ride:** You can ask the driver to \"pause\" the ride while you complete your errand or activity. This will keep the trip ongoing, and you can continue the ride back afterward.\n\n### 2. **Use Uber\u2019s Wait Time Feature:**\n   - **Add a Stop:** While booking your ride, you can add a stop at your destination. This will allow you to have the driver wait for you while you complete your task. Be aware that Uber charges for wait times, so this could increase the cost of your ride.\n   - **Return Trip:** After completing your task, you can continue the ride back to your original location. This way, the entire trip is counted as a single ride.\n\n### 3. **Book a Scheduled Ride:**\n   - **Schedule in Advance:** If you know your timeline, you can schedule a ride in advance and coordinate with the driver for a round trip. This is not a guaranteed feature, but some drivers may be willing to accommodate.\n\n### 4. **Use Uber Reserve:**\n   - **Uber Reserve:** In some markets, Uber offers a premium service called Uber Reserve, which allows you to book a ride in advance with a set wait time. You can use this service to arrange a round trip with a driver who is willing to wait.\n\n### 5. **Contact Uber Support:**\n   - **Special Request:** You can contact Uber support through the app and explain your situation. They may be able to assist you in setting up a round trip with a driver who is willing to accommodate your request.\n\n### Important Considerations:\n- **Wait Time Charges:** Be aware that if the driver waits for you, you will be charged for the wait time. This can add to the overall cost of the trip.\n- **Driver Availability:** Not all drivers may be willing or able to wait for a round trip, so it\u2019s important to communicate your needs clearly and in advance.\n- **Alternative Options:** If a round trip is essential, consider booking two separate rides (one to your destination and one back). This ensures you have a ride back, even if it\u2019s not counted as a single trip.\n\nWhile Uber doesn\u2019t officially offer a round trip feature, these workarounds can help you achieve a similar result. Always communicate your needs clearly with the driver to ensure a smooth experience.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
